2) Dollar and Euro Exchange Rates with the Searches on Google

This data set involves the Euro and Dollar rates according to Turkish Lira with a daily basis. The data is started from 01.01.2016 to 01.01.2021. Since the time frame is so long to interpret daily, it is obvious that we have to change its time frame from daily to monthly for line plots. Since Euro and Dollar are generally moved together, their oscillitions will be observed which is in an increasing trend over the last decade.

It is very clear that Euro and Dollar rates move together according to Turkish Lira. Since it is an economic and governmental situation, things that make Turkey economics lead worse, lead exchange rates upwards. Comparing the results with the Google searches would be wise. For example, letâs investigate key word â1 Dolarâ in Google Trends. Because Google has a currency converter, people may be searching for the answer in Google.

It is obvious that increasing in dollar and increasing in the search volume of the â1 Dolarâ are correlated because a sudden increase in dollar prices are important for the people. These importance lead them to search more while the Dollar increases. These situations are also accurate for the movement of the Euro and the search volume of the â1 Euroâ For all aspects of the trends, an increase that does not exceed the trend lines does not bother people. For our example of Dollar rate over Turkish Lira, in September 2018 there is an enormous and sudden increase for the prices which made people aware. Also, awareness lead people to wonder and search dollar prices in Google. The next big step in the searches is the December 2020, which is another exceeding from the trend. Comparing these two highs which are, 09.2018 and 12.2020, in the first one people searched more that the second one. The reason behind that is in 2018, the deviation from the trend was way bigger than in the 2020.
